me.Salt.Command.Commands.Fun.CardsAgainstDiscord

Class CaDRemovePlayerCommand

  • java.lang.Object
    • me.Salt.Command.Command
      • me.Salt.Command.Commands.Fun.CardsAgainstDiscord.CaDRemovePlayerCommand
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ICommand

    public class CaDRemovePlayerCommand
extends Command
implements ICommand
    This command is used to remove a player from a Cards Against Discord game. As would be expected, the command executor must not only have a Cards Against Discord game session, but the session must also contain the specified player.

    This command requires one parameter minimum. The parameter must be either u: or id:, where either a full username or a user's ID must be immediately appended, respectively. For example, the following command would remove a user with the username user1 and a user with the ID of 203182861401063425 from the game - if they are in the game: .cadremove u:user1 id:203182861401063425

    A list of those removed is returned to the command executor.
